H0.text: What name is given to the elements with atomic numbers from 89 to 103 in the periodic table. Neptunide

H1.text: What name is given to the elements with atomic numbers from 89 to 103 in the periodic table. Transuranic Series

H2.text: What name is given to the elements with atomic numbers from 89 to 103 in the periodic table. Radioactive Metals

H3.text: What name is given to the elements with atomic numbers from 89 to 103 in the periodic table. Actinide

A4.text: Number 103, lawrencium, is also generally included in the actinide series.

A5.text: The actinide series encompasses the 14 metallic chemical elements in the 5f series, with atomic numbers from 89 to 102, actinium through nobelium.
